    * Moldauer width fluctuation correction/19/ was included.     9861 1451
    * Neutron, gamma and fission decay channel were included.     9861 1451
    * Transmission coefficients of neutrons were taken from       9861 1451
      coupled channel calculation in Table 1.                     9861 1451
    * The level scheme of the target is shown in Table 2.         9861 1451
    * Level density formula of constant temperature and Fermi-gas 9861 1451
      model were used with shell energy correction and collective 9861 1451
      enhancement factor. Parameters are shown in Table 3.        9861 1451
    * Fission channel:                                            9861 1451
      Double humped fission barriers were assumed.                9861 1451
      Fission barrier penetrabilities were calculated with        9861 1451
      Hill-Wheler formula/20/. Fission barrier parameters were    9861 1451
      shown in Table 4. Transition state model was used and       9861 1451
      continuum levels are assumed above the saddles. The level   9861 1451
      density parameters for inner and outer saddles are shown in 9861 1451
      Tables 5 and 6, respectively.                               9861 1451
    * Gamma-ray strength function of Kopecky et al/21/,/22/       9861 1451
